THE insurance sector has recorded a total asset of N2.14 trillion as against the N2.02 trillion. This figure was for last year, the Commissioner, the National Insurance Commission (NAICOM), Mr. Sunday Thomas, has said.   ‘Using data key to transforming SMEs’     Lagos to hold summit on youth unemployment     Deel: technology boosts hiring   He made this known in a statement. The sector’s unaudited Gross Premium Income (GPI), however, stood at N630,362.35 billion in 2021, as against audited N514 billion recorded the previous year, According to him, operators paid net claims of N238,050.49 billion in 2021. He noted that the figures were derived from the quarterly reports submitted by the operators in 2021.   SPONSORED